SAFA have appointed SA junior national teams' coach Molefi Ntseki to steer the ship in the interim. Ntseki takes over from Stuart Baxter who resigned on Friday.The Safa Technical Committee met on Saturday to map the way forward for the SA Senior National Team and they decided that in the interest of continuity, they should move swiftly in appointing Amajimbos (SA Under-17) coach Ntseki. He will oversee Bafana's upcoming friendly matches in starting in September. Ntseki has also worked with the SA Under-20 and also served as Baxter's assistant.